---
import StoryLayout from '../../layouts/StoryLayout.astro';
---

<StoryLayout
  source="Kellogg MBA"
  title="Built From a Problem I Lived Through"
  tags={['AIinMarketing', 'SystemsThinking', 'ProductFromInsight', 'MarketingOps', 'FutureOfMarketing']}
>
  <div style="position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%; height: 0; overflow: hidden;">
    <iframe
      src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/dxGvzl2LMWk"
      style="position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%;"
      frameborder="0"
      allowfullscreen
    ></iframe>
  </div>

  <p>
    A lot of brand managers leave in their first two years. Rarely because they aren't capable:
    more often because no one gave them a clear way to figure out what to work on first.
  </p>
  <p>
    I ran into this myself early at P&amp;G. At Kellogg, I built a system to address it: an
    AI-powered prioritization tool using n8n workflows and multi-agent AI that collects tasks,
    scores them by urgency and impact, and gives managers a clear daily view of what matters most.
    It's designed to bring structure to a role that often starts with none.
  </p>
  <p>The project won the Kellogg Future Unicorn Award.</p>
  <div class="result-highlight">
    <h2>Results</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Kellogg Future Unicorn Award</li>
      <li>Built working n8n + multi-agent AI workflow (not a concept, a running system)</li>
      <li>Designed to scale beyond brand management to any multi-stakeholder role</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

</StoryLayout>
